<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8676] It&apos;s not possible to use a different log4.properties file on windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8676</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s currently not possible to change the location of the log4j.properties file on windows. The value of &lt;tt&gt;LOG4J_CONFIG&lt;/tt&gt; always gets replaced with the default value &lt;tt&gt;server\resources\log4j.properties&lt;/tt&gt;. Thus, this file inside the server directory needs to be changed after every update.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See attached patch for a fix. Unfortunately, I couldn&apos;t figure out why &lt;tt&gt;LOG4J_CONFIG&lt;/tt&gt; was set to empty. I tested manually that logging still works when running an example so I hope that this line is really just obsolete.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
